{"about_the_game":"<h2 class=\"bb_tag\">Puzzles</h2><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1125880/extras/\ud37c\uc990.gif?t=1627995192\" /><br><br>LaserZone is a Sci-Fi, top-down puzzle game.<br>In this game, you will be playing as \u2018Handel\u2019;<br>the protagonist who finds himself trapped inside lethal puzzles, <br>and aims to escape by using his brainpower.<br><br>LaserZone uses easy-to-understand science concepts as puzzle mechanics. <br>For example,<br><br><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li>Rotate Prisms to <u>reflect</u> Lasers.<br></li><li>Exploit <u>velocity</u> and <u>force</u> from Moving Walks and Gravity Turrets to move objects.<br></li><li>Use Switches and EMP Gun to <u>power up and down</u> traps.  </li></ul><br>What you might have come across during science class in school, now returns as puzzles in a concise fashion.<br>This is the key feature of the LaserZone.<h2 class=\"bb_tag\">Actions</h2><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1125880/extras/\uc561\uc158.gif?t=1627995192\" /><br><br>Sometimes, in LaserZone, <u>reflexes</u> are crucial for your escape.<br><br><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li>Bullets force-open Item Boxes for you, but sometimes can form a dangerous barrage in certain maps.<br></li><li>Gravity Towers that push or pull objects may drive you into a Minefield.<br></li><li>If you somehow survived, then robots will appear to take you down.</li></ul><br>LaserZone is indeed about solving puzzles. <br>But sometimes, you\u2019ll need to fight and evade.<h2 class=\"bb_tag\">Tools and Upgrades</h2><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1125880/extras/\ub3c4\uad6c\uc640\uc2a4\ud0ac.png?t=1627995192\" /><br><br>As you continue the game, the difficulty will generally increase.<br>However, you will be given Tools and Upgrades to overcome any difficulties.<br><br>You may acquire a few equipment with luck, <br>but most upgrades will cost Resources which must be earned with effort.<h2 class=\"bb_tag\">Plot, Story &amp; Directing</h2><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1125880/extras/\ud50c\ub86f.jpg?t=1627995192\" /><br><br>Handel wakes up inside his crash-landed spaceship, suffering a loss of memory.<br>He searches nearby places to recover from amnesia and find usable parts for the spaceship.<br>Shortly, he sets his foot in an enormous facility, unknowing the existence of deadly traps lurking inside.<br>Will he be able to recover his memory, and reclaim the treasure greater than his own life?<br><br>Several characters including Handel will appear in LaserZone.<br>Handel talks with them, sometimes confront them, reminds himself of what happened in the past, and moves forward to end the journey once and for all.<h2 class=\"bb_tag\">Art</h2><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1125880/extras/\uc544\ud2b8\ub300\uccb4\uadf8\ub9bc2.jpg?t=1627995192\" /><br><br>LaserZone is a 2D game with a three-dimensional effect. It is built based on <u>Cycles Render</u> from Blender Cycles 3D Tool.<br><br>Thanks to Cycles Render's power, we have created a world brimming with futuristic artworks and Sci-Fi atmosphere.<br><br><br><i>* LaserZone uses free classic music as BGM, whose copyrights AND neighboring copyrights have expired.</i>","achievements":{"highlighted":[{"name":"Resources","path":"https://cdn.akamai.steamstatic.com/steamcommunity/public/images/apps/1125880/8603933c7be91ebf7838b580dde2f02c5b197dc1.jpg"},{"name":"Chapter 1 Completed","path":"https://cdn.akamai.steamstatic.com/steamcommunity/public/images/apps/1125880/8603933c7be91ebf7838b580dde2f02c5b197dc1.jpg"},{"name":"Chapter 2 Completed","path":"https://cdn.akamai.steamstatic.com/steamcommunity/public/images/apps/1125880/8603933c7be91ebf7838b580dde2f02c5b197dc1.jpg"},{"name":"Chapter 3 Completed","